==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: faker
<hw>fak"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sometimes erroneously
written <ets>fakir</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who fakes
something;</def> <specif>as</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>a thief.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd>, <def>a peddler of petty things.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>a
workman who dresses things up.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a person who makes deceitful pretenses.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> imposter, impostor, pretender, fake, fraud, sham,
pseudo, pseud, role player.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fakir</ent>⟦br⟧
